So I'm relatively new to this game...never been in a clan before, or anything like that. What's it like being in Death's Enclave? I meet the requirements to join but I'd like to have some better idea of what the clan does (and what clans do in general) before I join. Would someone be willing to tell me about it? And would you accept me if I joined?
On december 22, 2009
Molotov
Death's Enclave is a training ground, so most if not all of the members are new to clan wars, clans themselves, and/or the whole game. Everyone is working together to learn as they go and gather information and skills. New members are always welcomed and questions are always answered.

The ranking system is point-based, and no one gets a rank until they've donated something to the clan. Donations are a clan requirement, but we have members who are still working to gain gathering skills anyway. The only other requirements are participation and courtesy - and, every member, before they join, must have The Stamps so that they can be contacted in private if necessary.

We report to Death's Children, and their goals are our goals, particularly in wartime; every member of Death's Enclave is free to aim for Death's Children membership someday, but if anyone wants to stay and help run the clan for future trainees, they're welcome to do so. The best members go up for recommendation to DC and may or may not be recruited to move up into their ranks. The more a member contributes and the stronger they are, the more likely they are to make a name for themselves.
On december 22, 2009
Molotov
(Basically we're glad to have just about anyone who fulfills the requirements.)

On january 15, 2010
AndySQdancer
Exodusarn, look at the differnt skill trees on our clan pages. The skills that are identified as C are collector skills and allow your dinoz that learns them to collect ingredients of that type on some locations (again look at the ingredients page of our clan pages). Your dinoz can try to collect ingredients once each turn, but only once a turn, that he/she is at one of the places where that ingredient can be collected. You will get a special button allowing you to Harvest, Search, Excavate, Fish, or Hunt depending on the specific collecting skill which allows you to select one square of many to try to collect an ingredient. Hope this helps. They say also that Search Button is your friend., but I am not sure about the friendlyness of the button.

[896143]
It seems to me that part of the problem lies in the mathematics of the calculation of reputation:

R= ((500 + Points won) / (500 + Points lost)) ^ 0,8 * 100
When a clan retaliates, the defending clan's 'Points won' not only decreases, but the 'Points lost' increases as well. This makes the damage done seem "double". When DC got attacked by 4 clans, which they had good points on, not only did their 'Points won' decrease drastically (some 1300), but their 'Points lost' increased as well (some 1000), making their reputation plummet.

I'm not suggesting that retaliating clans should not take their loss back and gain new points as well, I am only proposing a change to the actual mathematics.
